==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Branlin
<hw>Bran"lin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot.
<ets>branlie</ets> fr. <ets>brand</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A young salmon or parr, in the stage in which it has transverse
black bands, as if burned by a gridiron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Branlin</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Branlin
<hw>Bran"lin</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Brand</er>.]</ety> <def>A
small red worm or larva, used as bait for small fresh-water fish; -- so
called from its red color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bran-new</ent>⟦br⟧
